title: Hispanic population of the U.S. 2000 to 2018
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Population in millions, containing a total of 19 data points.
In general Population in millions has rose over the Year.
Population in millions is slightly increasing from 2000 to 2014, and lastly roughly constant from 2014 to 2018.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2006 and 2007.
Maximum Population in millions, about 59.87 was reported at Year 2018
The lowest Population in millions, of value 35.66 was reported at Year 2000
